
[1]buckle

   BUCK'LE, n.

   1. An instrument made of some kind of metal, for fastening together
   certain parts of dress, as the straps and bands, as in a harness. The
   forms are various, but it consists of a ring or rim with a chape and
   tongue.

   2. A curl, or a state of being curled or crisped, as hair.

   3. In coats of arms, a token of the surety, faith and service of the
   bearer.

              BUCK'LE, v.t. To fasten with a buckle,or buckles.

   1. To prepare for action; a metaphor, taken from buckling on armor.

   2. To join in battle.

   3. To confine or limit

   A span buckles in his sum of age.
